body: Can you share a small code snippet ? What is the error you get in Eval() when you try using a pointer ?

"Non-zero status code returned while running Shape node." This means what you intended to do (i.e.) run the model went through just fine. 

The complaint is about a Shape node in the model/graph. It could either be a model issue (converter bug) or a bug in ORT itself. If you could create a simple model and share it to repro, we can investigate further.
Thanks @hariharans29 ! I tried Unique smart pointer and found it works for this case to hold pointer to Ort::Session instead of shared_ptr.
Did you use a different model or the same model when you switched to using unique_ptr ? From the earlier error message, it seemed to point to an error while actually running the model...
@hariharans29 , the same model for unique/share pointer. All the other logic (load/run session, etc...) are not changed.

Why don;t you just hold Ort::Session by value? The object has the only member - a pointer to the underlying structure and exists for automatic cleanup purposes. It itself acts as a smart pointer, there is not a need to wrap it into another smart ptr.

@yuslepukhin Tried to hold Session by value but Operator= is banned for Ort::Session, and I haven't found a member for this object to hold reference. Could you share a code snip for better understanding your suggestion ?
Please reopen this issue if you need more help.
